\par
\par
{\b\fs26 Near-term (first implementation)}\par
\par
\li360  \u8226?  [ ] {\b Define the input feature matrix spec}: `feature_id | feature_source |\par
      feature_type | origin_zone | species_1 | ... | species_N`. Loaded from STEP_1's\par
      per-structure summaries.\par
\li360  \u8226?  [ ] {\b Implement total-loss aggregator}: per topology, sum Loss events across all\par
      features. Output: {\f1 structure_ranking.tsv} with columns `structure_id | total_loss\par
      | rank | is_user_tree`.\par
\li360  \u8226?  [ ] {\b Implement 4/5 clade representation filter}: features present in 4 of 5\par
      unresolved clades are "discriminating"; included. 5/5 features are "controls";\par
      tracked separately for diagnostics. Features with <4/5 either rejected or\par
      flagged for LBA-at-clustering risk.\par
\li360  \u8226?  [ ] {\b Implement bootstrap-analog subsampling}: N subsamples of features,\par
      recompute ranking, report per-topology "ranked first in X% of subsamples".\par
\li360  \u8226?  [ ] {\b Per-topology detail table}: {\f1 per_structure_loss_detail.tsv} \u8212? which features\par
      contributed how many losses to each structure's score. Essential for diagnosis.\par
